reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 14, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great compact and comprehensive first aid kit
reviews.reviewText: Contained everything that was required by OSHA for the purpose we needed. Portable,good instructions,well labled

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 9, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Very complete and filled with lots of excellent safety supplies.
reviews.reviewText: I was so impressed with the contents of this kit that I purchased four of them as Christmas gifts: one each for my son, daughter,son-in-law, and granddaughter for each to keep in their vehicle to help keep them safe. The kit has a lot of extra non-medical supplies such as a compass and a heated blanket. Very pleased with this product! I added an Automotive Escape Tool that included a Window Breaker Seat belt Cutter, Car Flashlight, and Safety Hammer to ensure my family members safety.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 7, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Compact First Aid Kit - Has Almost Everything!
reviews.reviewText: This is a great, compact kit that fits into a backpack and is ready to use. It has just about everything you need for a minor first aid issue. Highly recommended.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on July 11, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Great kit for the price
reviews.reviewText: I have used this kit SEVERAL times since I ordered it a year ago. It is small enough to easily fit in my truck. My only complaint is that while there is plenty of disinfectant, there isn't any ointment like Neosporin included. I bought some Amazon brand neosporin to round out this kit, otherwise it's perfect for simple burns, cuts, etc.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 3, 2023
reviews.reviewText: it's great, I unfortunately happened to injure myself, and it was a great time to test out my new first aid kit.it came with a lot of "survival" things, like a compass and other small things. but on the medical side, it comes with wipes to clean off any injuries, and comes with many different sizes of bandaids to fit many different types of minor injuries. luckily I came out of this with only a scrape on my knee, and my ego bruised. but luckily I had everything to properly clean out the concrete from my scrapes.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 24, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great for work scenarios that are outside, or for long distance hiking
reviews.reviewText: The packs are well packed, with additional items that are needed for outside emergencies.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 11, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Good idea to have on your bike
reviews.reviewText: I bought this to have on my motorcycle for "just in case". I hope I never need to use it, But its there if I need it. Price is good and it has pretty much everything you need if you lay it down.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 26, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars School office kit. Had everything we thought we would need being a small school.
reviews.reviewText: Just what we needed for our small school. We did not have a first aid kit in the office and this kit was just the right size. Ordered a second one for our gym to have something available at athletic contests we hosted.
